1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,853
Hello, friends!

2
00:00:00,853 --> 00:00:04,384
On the night of December 3, 1984, 
at approximately midnight,

3
00:00:04,384 --> 00:00:07,026
In Bhopal's train station Bhopal Junction 

4
00:00:07,026 --> 00:00:09,195
the station superintendent H.S. Bhurvey

5
00:00:09,195 --> 00:00:11,304
and the deputy station superintendent

6
00:00:11,304 --> 00:00:14,205
Ghulam Dastagir were on duty.

7
00:00:14,572 --> 00:00:15,997
Around 1 o'clock,

8
00:00:15,997 --> 00:00:19,240
the Gorakhpur-Bombay Express arrived at the station,

9
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:21,664
prompting Dastagir to leave his cabin.

10
00:00:21,664 --> 00:00:26,898
Suddenly, he experienced burning eyes and a sore throat.

11
00:00:28,527 --> 00:00:31,972
Concerned, he searched for Bhurvey, 
his superior, to inform him about this,

12
00:00:31,972 --> 00:00:33,393
but couldn't find him.

13
00:00:33,393 --> 00:00:36,935
Moments later, he found Bhurvey lying on the ground.

14
00:00:36,935 --> 00:00:39,936
Dastagir tried to check whether he was breathing,

15
00:00:39,936 --> 00:00:42,499
but realized that Bhurvey had passed away.

16
00:00:42,499 --> 00:00:46,081
Dastagir immediately understood the cause

17
00:00:46,081 --> 00:00:50,335
The thing is that, a kilometre away from Bhopal Junction,

18
00:00:50,335 --> 00:00:52,618
in the Union Carbide factory

19
00:00:52,618 --> 00:00:54,850
there had been a hazardous incident,

20
00:00:56,318 --> 00:01:01,632
releasing 50,000 pounds of poisonous gas,

21
00:01:01,632 --> 00:01:05,843
including MIC, hydrogen cyanide, and phosgene.

22
00:01:05,843 --> 00:01:10,336
The gases were spreading rapidly all over the city.

23
00:01:10,336 --> 00:01:13,668
As the most senior person present, Dastagir took charge,

24
00:01:13,668 --> 00:01:20,708
deciding that the Gorakhpur-bound train 
needed to leave before its scheduled departure,

25
00:01:20,708 --> 00:01:24,499
even though it was supposed to 
stay at the station for 20 more minutes.

26
00:01:24,499 --> 00:01:27,080
The passengers of the train had the windows closed,

27
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:29,079
and Dastagir didn't want 

28
00:01:29,079 --> 00:01:31,381
the passengers to be harmed in any way.

29
00:01:31,381 --> 00:01:33,767
With passengers' safety in mind, 
Dastagir broke protocol

30
00:01:33,767 --> 00:01:38,083
and ordered the station staff to 
clear the way for an early departure.

31
00:01:38,083 --> 00:01:42,315
And he assumed all responsibilities of breaking this protocol.

32
00:01:42,315 --> 00:01:46,622
Meanwhile, the crowd at the station was growing.

33
00:01:46,622 --> 00:01:50,091
The incident occurred during the night 
when most people were asleep at home.

34
00:01:50,091 --> 00:01:52,224
Some individuals, facing difficulty breathing,

35
00:01:52,224 --> 00:01:56,742
took refuge in their cars and tried to leave the city.

36
00:01:56,742 --> 00:01:59,161
But on the other hand, those without vehicles

37
00:01:59,161 --> 00:02:02,079
gathered at the station,

38
00:02:02,079 --> 00:02:03,979
unsure of what to do.

39
00:02:03,979 --> 00:02:06,962
More and more people kept coming to Bhopal Junction.

40
00:02:06,962 --> 00:02:11,657
People were coughing, crying, 
and vomiting all around the station.

41
00:02:11,657 --> 00:02:15,231
Dastagir was running from one platform to the other,

42
00:02:15,231 --> 00:02:19,227
trying to help the people in any way he could.

43
00:02:19,227 --> 00:02:22,125
He made an SOS call to the nearby stations,

44
00:02:22,125 --> 00:02:27,474
after which, 4 ambulances, paramedics, and 
railway doctors reached the station to help people.

45
00:02:27,474 --> 00:02:30,723
Despite all efforts, escaping the poisonous gas proved challenging.

46
00:02:44,053 --> 00:02:48,105
While on one hand, some had fled 
their homes to reach the station,

47
00:02:48,105 --> 00:02:51,942
on the other hand, more people headed to hospitals.

48
00:02:51,942 --> 00:02:57,209
Obviously, if someone experiences burning eyes 
and breathing difficulties while sleeping at night,

49
00:02:57,209 --> 00:02:59,019
they'll go to a hospital.

50
00:02:59,019 --> 00:03:00,612
However, the challenge was that

51
00:03:00,612 --> 00:03:03,824
neither the railway doctors nor the hospital staff understood

52
00:03:03,824 --> 00:03:05,262
the nature of the situation.

53
00:03:05,262 --> 00:03:08,401
These symptoms were unfamiliar to them,

54
00:03:08,401 --> 00:03:13,031
and they struggled to identify the illness or its cause.

55
00:03:13,031 --> 00:03:15,941
3 km from the Union Carbide factory,

56
00:03:15,941 --> 00:03:17,995
was Bhopal's Hamidia Hospital.

57
00:03:17,995 --> 00:03:22,316
At the time, the hospital had a capacity of approximately 1,200 beds.

58
00:03:22,316 --> 00:03:24,224
Around 1:15 AM,

59
00:03:24,224 --> 00:03:26,552
the first patient arrived,

60
00:03:26,552 --> 00:03:29,530
complaining of eye irritation.

61
00:03:29,530 --> 00:03:31,471
Within the next five minutes,

62
00:03:31,471 --> 00:03:34,930
over 1000 people had gathered at the hospital.

63
00:03:34,930 --> 00:03:39,077
Some doctors attempted to obtain 
information from the union carbide factory

64
00:03:39,077 --> 00:03:42,870
but they didn't provide any useful information. 

65
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:45,864
The company's medical officer, L.D. Loya told the doctors

66
00:03:45,864 --> 00:03:48,009
that the gas was not poisonous

67
00:03:48,009 --> 00:03:51,695
and advised the application of 
wet bandages to the eyes.

68
00:03:51,695 --> 00:03:55,458
Meanwhile, the Superintendent of Police, 
Swaraj Puri, visited the control room 

69
00:03:55,458 --> 00:04:00,644
and saw that his staff was coughing 
helplessly and rubbing their eyes.

70
00:04:00,644 --> 00:04:03,616
That was around 1:25 AM.

71
00:04:03,616 --> 00:04:06,091
He called the carbide factory.

72
00:04:06,091 --> 00:04:08,181
on the first two phone calls, 
he received assurances of

73
00:04:08,181 --> 00:04:10,170
everything being okay.

74
00:04:10,170 --> 00:04:12,197
However, after the third call,

75
00:04:12,197 --> 00:04:13,893
the response was uncertain:

76
00:04:13,893 --> 00:04:15,603
the people at the factory claimed that 
they didn't know what had happened.

77
00:04:15,603 --> 00:04:17,262
"We don't know what has happened."

78
00:04:17,262 --> 00:04:19,714
By 2:10 AM,

79
00:04:19,714 --> 00:04:24,077
the hospital had admitted around 4,000 patients,

80
00:04:24,077 --> 00:04:27,349
and chaos was unfolding at Bhopal Junction Station.

81
00:04:27,349 --> 00:04:31,390
Dastagir had ensured that the 
Gorakhpur Bombay Express had left the station,

82
00:04:31,390 --> 00:04:34,654
but aiding people became increasingly challenging.

83
00:04:34,654 --> 00:04:37,809
He later learned that his senior, H.S. Bhurvey,

84
00:04:37,809 --> 00:04:41,695
had lost his life while directing another train to leave Bhopal,

85
00:04:41,695 --> 00:04:45,877
his senior had instructed the train not to stop at the platform.

86
00:04:45,877 --> 00:04:48,152
And to keep moving.

87
00:04:48,152 --> 00:04:50,612
Ghulam Dastagir, his wife, and their 4 children,

88
00:04:50,612 --> 00:04:52,839
lived in old Bhopal.

89
00:04:52,839 --> 00:04:57,217
Merely 3 km from the Union Carbide factory.

90
00:04:57,217 --> 00:05:00,807
But Dasgir didn't leave the station to check on his family.

91
00:05:00,807 --> 00:05:03,929
He remained at the station, 
dedicated to assisting those in need.

92
00:05:03,929 --> 00:05:07,757
Trains arriving at the station were prevented from stopping

93
00:05:07,757 --> 00:05:08,842
they were asked to keep going.

94
00:05:08,842 --> 00:05:12,280
Manzoor Ahmed Khan, Dasgir's colleague, was

95
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:14,629
among the individuals arriving at the station to leave Bhopal.

96
00:05:14,629 --> 00:05:18,913
Around 3 AM, he arrived at the station with their entire family.

97
00:05:18,913 --> 00:05:23,129
Observing Dastagir tirelessly moving from platform to platform,

98
00:05:23,129 --> 00:05:27,980
assisting people selflessly without concern 
for his own safety or that of his family.

