This series is the first series by Yash Raj Entertainment to be released on an OTT platform.

104
00:05:43,890 --> 00:05:46,066
Watching the trailer will give you 

105
00:05:46,066 --> 00:05:50,836
a clear sense of the suspense and thrill 
embedded in the story of that night in this series.

106
00:05:50,836 --> 00:05:54,006
On one hand, the doctors and paramedics at the stations and hospitals

107
00:05:54,006 --> 00:05:57,539
were working tirelessly to save lives.

108
00:05:57,539 --> 00:06:01,136
On the other hand, they didn't truly know

109
00:06:01,136 --> 00:06:04,001
how to treat the cause of the symptoms. 

110
00:06:04,001 --> 00:06:08,547
Most of the doctors administered eye drops 
to reduce the burning sensation in the eyes,

111
00:06:08,547 --> 00:06:10,473
steroids to treat the inflammation,

112
00:06:10,473 --> 00:06:13,841
and antibiotics to prevent secondary infection,

113
00:06:13,841 --> 00:06:16,595
and antacids to treat stomach problems.

114
00:06:16,595 --> 00:06:18,874
The real solution, though,

115
00:06:18,874 --> 00:06:21,473
depended on identifying the gas.

116
00:06:21,473 --> 00:06:26,228
Whether it was MIC, Phosgene, 
or another gas like hydrogen cyanide.

117
00:06:26,228 --> 00:06:28,875
Initially, doctors suspected phosgene poisoning,

118
00:06:28,875 --> 00:06:32,982
because there was a similar incident 3 years prior to this

119
00:06:32,982 --> 00:06:35,822
in the same Union Carbide factory.

120
00:06:35,822 --> 00:06:37,943
In December 1981,

121
00:06:37,943 --> 00:06:41,325
resulting in the d3ath of a person working in 
this factory, Ashraf Muhammad Khan.

122
00:06:41,325 --> 00:06:43,338
Due to a phosgene leak.

123
00:06:43,338 --> 00:06:47,957
Conversely, the company downplayed the severity, claiming it was MIC

124
00:06:47,957 --> 00:06:51,080
and advising simple remedies like wet bandages for eye irritation.

125
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:54,241
Notably, MIC vaporizes at 38°C,

126
00:06:54,241 --> 00:06:56,046
a considerably high temperature. 

127
00:06:56,046 --> 00:06:59,287
Whereas phosgene vaporizes at 8°C.

128
00:06:59,287 --> 00:07:01,608
Given the December climate in Bhopal,

129
00:07:01,608 --> 00:07:04,307
doctors assumed phosgene to be the culprit,

130
00:07:04,307 --> 00:07:08,037
No one knew that at the time of this incident in the factory,

131
00:07:08,037 --> 00:07:11,725
the factory's temperature was around 400°C.

132
00:07:11,725 --> 00:07:14,847
Meanwhile, in America, Carbide's medical director, Bipin Awasia,

133
00:07:14,847 --> 00:07:16,641
informed Bhopal authorities

134
00:07:16,641 --> 00:07:18,881
that if cyanide poisoning was suspected,

135
00:07:18,881 --> 00:07:23,190
sodium thiosulfate should be administered as an antidote.

136
00:07:23,190 --> 00:07:25,834
In earlier experiments it was observed that

137
00:07:25,834 --> 00:07:29,805
MIC breaks down into hydrogen cyanide during combustion,

138
00:07:29,805 --> 00:07:35,229
And hydrogen cyanide could be countered 
effectively by sodium thiosulfate.

139
00:07:35,229 --> 00:07:41,983
But Bipin Awasia retracted his statement 10 days 
later during a press conference in Bhopal,

140
00:07:41,983 --> 00:07:44,538
asserting that there was no cyanide poisoning,

141
00:07:44,538 --> 00:07:46,291
rendering the antidote useless.

142
00:07:46,291 --> 00:07:48,545
The company issued a statement

143
00:07:48,545 --> 00:07:50,827
clarifying that MIC is not cyanide,

144
00:07:50,827 --> 00:07:52,610
and that the two should not be confused.

145
00:07:52,610 --> 00:07:55,769
emphasizing that MIC naturally degrades into the environment

146
00:07:55,769 --> 00:07:57,515
when exposed to water.

147
00:07:57,515 --> 00:08:00,425
However, this clarification from the company was very late.

148
00:08:00,425 --> 00:08:04,998
by then, numerous patients were 
in the hospital awaiting treatment.

149
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:07,251
To help the distressed patients,

150
00:08:07,251 --> 00:08:11,041
on December 8th, German toxicologist Max Daunderer,

151
00:08:11,041 --> 00:08:15,143
arrived in Bhopal with 50,000 doses of sodium thiosulfate.

152
00:08:15,143 --> 00:08:18,289
When doctors used sodium thiosulfate, 

153
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:20,722
it proved quite successful,

154
00:08:20,722 --> 00:08:23,340
with many patients recovering.

155
00:08:23,340 --> 00:08:26,143
Unfortunately, one patient d!ed after its administration.

156
00:08:26,143 --> 00:08:27,460
This led to widespread rumours that

157
00:08:27,460 --> 00:08:31,412
a German doctor had k!lled a patient with sodium thiosulfate.

158
00:08:31,412 --> 00:08:35,724
Consequently, the doctor and his antidotes were sent back.

159
00:08:35,724 --> 00:08:40,744
Senior professors at Gandhi Medical College 
rejected the use of sodium thiosulfate.

160
00:08:40,744 --> 00:08:45,220
Dr. M. N. Nagu, the director of Madhya Pradesh's health services at the time,

161
00:08:45,220 --> 00:08:47,484
published a circular on 13th December stating that

162
00:08:47,484 --> 00:08:51,618
"under no circumstances shall sodium thiosulfate be given

163
00:08:51,618 --> 00:08:55,077
unless it is correctly and conclusively proved in the laboratory 

164
00:08:55,077 --> 00:08:56,995
that it is cyanide poisoning."

165
00:08:56,995 --> 00:08:59,065
Despite this stance, some remained convinced that

166
00:08:59,065 --> 00:09:01,295
these patients were suffering from cyanide poisoning.

167
00:09:01,295 --> 00:09:05,130
First because when sodium thiosulfate 
was being administered on some patients,

168
00:09:05,130 --> 00:09:07,689
positive effects were observed.

169
00:09:07,689 --> 00:09:12,435
And second because when Bhopal Medical 
Legal Institute's Director, Dr Hirish Chandra, 

170
00:09:12,435 --> 00:09:14,007
conducted autopsies on the bodies,

171
00:09:14,007 --> 00:09:16,727
he found evidence of cyanide poisoning.

172
00:09:16,727 --> 00:09:19,890
He reiterated that sodium thiosulfate should be used.

173
00:09:19,890 --> 00:09:22,031
Weeks later, in February,

174
00:09:22,031 --> 00:09:24,362
ICMR instructed doctors

175
00:09:24,362 --> 00:09:26,406
to use sodium thiosulfate.

176
00:09:26,406 --> 00:09:30,106
The biggest question here was:
Why was there so much confusion?

177
00:09:30,106 --> 00:09:33,412
The company that owned the factory,

178
00:09:33,412 --> 00:09:37,461
why did they create so much confusion
about MIC and cyanide?

179
00:09:37,461 --> 00:09:39,636
The direct answer is:

180
00:09:39,636 --> 00:09:42,228
The company was in the midst of a huge compensation claim,

181
00:09:42,228 --> 00:09:46,463
they wanted to minimize the side effects of MIC to save money.

182
00:09:46,463 --> 00:09:49,081
Government authorities were also caught in this confusion,

183
00:09:49,081 --> 00:09:52,729
resulting in the unfortunate d3ath of many 
individuals who could have been saved

184
00:09:52,729 --> 00:09:55,845
had they received the correct and timely treatment.

185
00:09:55,845 --> 00:09:59,246
Ghulam Dasgir, the person I talked about at the beginning of this video,

186
00:09:59,246 --> 00:10:01,646
managed to save himself.

187
00:10:01,646 --> 00:10:04,346
But the last 19 years of his life

188
00:10:04,346 --> 00:10:07,038
were mostly spent in the hospital,

189
00:10:07,038 --> 00:10:09,736
he passed away in 2003.

190
00:10:09,736 --> 00:10:13,392
What makes the Bhopal gas tragedy 
particularly shocking is that

191
00:10:13,392 --> 00:10:19,100
numerous warnings by various people 
had been given before the incident.

192
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:20,400
Many had voiced concerns,

193
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:22,268
alerting authorities that the factory posed a constant danger

194
00:10:22,268 --> 00:10:25,005
due to the lack of safety measures.

195
00:10:25,005 --> 00:10:28,241
Regrettably, neither the company nor the government authorities

196
00:10:28,241 --> 00:10:29,973
took any preventive action.

197
00:10:29,973 --> 00:10:34,711
In 1981, when Ashraf Khan lost his life in a Carbide accident,

198
00:10:34,711 --> 00:10:39,849
three experts from the US, were sent
by the company in May 1982,

199
00:10:39,849 --> 00:10:43,304
to assess the plant's safety measures.

200
00:10:43,304 --> 00:10:47,678
Their report identified over 60 hazards,

201
00:10:47,678 --> 00:10:49,249
highlighting issues such as

202
00:10:49,249 --> 00:10:54,890
the emergency evacuation procedures weren't 
shared with the people living near the factory.

203
00:10:54,890 --> 00:11:00,370
and that the MIC tanks could be easily contaminated.

204
00:11:00,370 --> 00:11:02,446
The tank pressure gauge was apparently defective.

205
00:11:02,446 --> 00:11:06,342
The issues and warnings raised in this report

206
00:11:06,342 --> 00:11:08,170
were published in three articles.

207
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:10,761
[Save This City]

208
00:11:10,761 --> 00:11:13,274
[Bhopal is Sitting on a Volcano's Mouth]

209
00:11:13,274 --> 00:11:16,670
[You'll Perish If You Don't Take This Seriously] 

210
00:11:16,670 --> 00:11:19,511
These articles were published in a local newspaper, Rajpath

211
00:11:19,511 --> 00:11:24,484
by a journalist Rajkumar Keswani within two weeks,

212
00:11:24,484 --> 00:11:28,403
Keshwani's last article on the Bhopal plant,

213
00:11:28,403 --> 00:11:31,396
was published on June 16, 1984,

214
00:11:31,396 --> 00:11:33,523
in the national newspaper Jansatta,

215
00:11:33,523 --> 00:11:38,735
warning of a situation of looming disaster in Bhopal.

216
00:11:38,735 --> 00:11:41,081
This underscores the vital role of

217
00:11:41,081 --> 00:11:44,436
independent and free media in the country.

218
00:11:44,436 --> 00:11:47,914
The truth is, Keswani didn't do anything extraordinary. 

219
00:11:47,914 --> 00:11:51,902
He simply carried out his job with honesty.

220
00:11:51,902 --> 00:11:55,160
And that's why, today he emerges as an unsung hero.

221
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:58,067
In his last article, he made another major revelation,

222
00:11:58,067 --> 00:12:01,486
that in 1975, Bhopal Municipal Corporation

223
00:12:01,486 --> 00:12:05,137
was headed by a highly respected bureaucrat MN Buch.

224
00:12:05,137 --> 00:12:08,900
He had issued a notice to remove Carbide from Bhopal.

225
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:12,040
Consequently, Buch was transferred,

226
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:15,613
and Carbide paid ₹25,000 to the Corporation

227
00:12:15,613 --> 00:12:17,562
for the construction of a public park.

228
00:12:17,562 --> 00:12:19,754
With this Keswani hinted at

229
00:12:19,754 --> 00:12:23,164
a collusion within the government to aid Carbide

230
00:12:23,164 --> 00:12:25,825
in successfully continuing its factory operations.

